# AdminLTE v3 Buttons - Official Patterns

## Base Button Structure

**All buttons must start with the `.btn` class:**

```html
<button type="button" class="btn btn-primary">Primary Button</button>
```

**Official Reference:** https://adminlte.io/themes/v3/pages/UI/buttons.html

---

## Solid Button Colors (Filled Background)

Use these classes for buttons with solid background colors:

```html
<button class="btn btn-primary">Primary</button>
<button class="btn btn-secondary">Secondary</button>
<button class="btn btn-success">Success</button>
<button class="btn btn-info">Info</button>
<button class="btn btn-danger">Danger</button>
<button class="btn btn-warning">Warning</button>
<button class="btn btn-light">Light</button>
<button class="btn btn-dark">Dark</button>
```

---

## Outline Buttons (Border Only - Recommended for Cancel/Reset)

Use `.btn-outline-*` for buttons with **borders only** (no background fill). These are perfect for secondary actions like "Cancel" or "Discard".

```html
<!-- Light border (gray) -->
<button class="btn btn-outline-secondary">Secondary Outline</button>

<!-- Dark border (recommended for cancel buttons) -->
<button class="btn btn-outline-dark">Dark Outline</button>

<!-- Other outline options -->
<button class="btn btn-outline-primary">Primary Outline</button>
<button class="btn btn-outline-success">Success Outline</button>
<button class="btn btn-outline-danger">Danger Outline</button>
```

### Color Reference (from AdminLTE v3 CSS):

```css
.btn-outline-secondary {
  color: #6c757d;           /* Lighter gray text */
  border-color: #6c757d;    /* Lighter gray border */
}

.btn-outline-dark {
  color: #343a40;           /* Dark gray text */
  border-color: #343a40;    /* Dark gray border ← More prominent */
}
```

**When to use `.btn-outline-dark`:**
- Cancel/Discard buttons (secondary action)
- Reset form buttons
- Back buttons
- Any non-primary action

**When to use `.btn-outline-secondary`:**
- Slightly less prominent alternative action
- When you want a lighter gray appearance

