## Button Alignment and Spacing

### Icon + Text Alignment Issue

**Problem:** Icons and text in buttons are often misaligned vertically.

**Solution:** Use flexbox on buttons to properly center icons and text:

```css
.btn {
    display: inline-flex;    /* Use flexbox instead of inline */
    align-items: center;     /* Center items vertically */
    gap: 6px;                /* Space between icon and text */
}
```

**Result:**
- ✅ Icon and text perfectly centered
- ✅ Consistent alignment across all buttons
- ✅ Works with any icon library (FontAwesome, etc.)

### Button Group Spacing

When you have multiple buttons in a row (like Cancel + Submit), add margin to create space:

```css
/* Space between buttons when they're next to each other */
.btn-group .btn {
    margin-right: 10px; /* Or use gap in flex container */
}

/* Or use margin on specific buttons */
#btn-discard {
    margin-right: 10px;
}
```

**HTML:**
```html
<div class="float-right">
    <!-- Buttons will have space between them -->
    <button class="btn btn-outline-dark" id="btn-discard">
        <i class="fas fa-times"></i> Descartar
    </button>
    <button class="btn btn-primary">
        <i class="fas fa-save"></i> Guardar
    </button>
</div>
```

**Better approach using flexbox:**
```html
<div class="float-right d-flex gap-2">
    <!-- Bootstrap utility classes handle spacing -->
    <button class="btn btn-outline-dark">
        <i class="fas fa-times"></i> Descartar
    </button>
    <button class="btn btn-primary">
        <i class="fas fa-save"></i> Guardar
    </button>
</div>
```

