## Common Patterns

### Form Action Buttons (Best Practice)

```html
<div class="card-footer">
    <div class="float-right">
        <!-- Cancel/Discard: Use outline-dark -->
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-outline-dark" id="btn-discard">
            <i class="fas fa-times"></i> Descartar
        </button>

        <!-- Submit: Use primary with solid background -->
        <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary">
            <i class="far fa-envelope"></i> Enviar
        </button>
    </div>
</div>
```

**Why this pattern?**
- ✅ Primary action (submit) is visually prominent
- ✅ Secondary action (discard) is visually de-emphasized
- ✅ Follows AdminLTE v3 official recommendations
- ✅ Dark outline border is clear and professional
- ✅ Icons and text properly aligned with flexbox
- ✅ Adequate spacing between buttons (10px margin)

### With Icons

AdminLTE v3 includes FontAwesome icons by default:

```html
<!-- Success with icon -->
<button class="btn btn-success">
    <i class="fas fa-check"></i> Guardar
</button>

<!-- Delete/Danger with icon -->
<button class="btn btn-danger">
    <i class="fas fa-trash"></i> Eliminar
</button>

<!-- Discard with icon -->
<button class="btn btn-outline-dark">
    <i class="fas fa-times"></i> Descartar
</button>
```

